    "The labels of each sub-cluster are also shown radially.",
    "When the user selects any cluster, the mentioned keywords are highlighted (T2).",
    "Under such cases, hovering over the keyword clusters will show not only the cluster label but also the highlighted keywords in a list, as shown in Figure 3-a.",
    "Users can also select a keyword to filter the articles in the Document View (T3).2) Expansion: Users can break a cluster into smaller clusters so that a deeper level of topic structures can be explored (T1).",
    "This operation is necessary since the agglomerative clustering result is not always semantically optimal, and some clusters may be too vague for the user."
